h1. Confluence Formatting Samples

h2. Panel Color Examples

h3. Information Panel
{panel:borderColor=blue|titleBGColor=blue|title=Blue Information Panel}
This is a blue panel typically used for key definitions, core concepts, and important informational content.
* Key point one
* Key point two
{panel}

h3. Warning Panel
{panel:borderColor=red|titleBGColor=red|title=Red Warning Panel}
Critical information or potential risks that require immediate attention.
* Urgent consideration
* High-priority item
{panel}

h3. Success Panel
{panel:borderColor=green|titleBGColor=green|title=Green Success Panel}
Positive outcomes, best practices, or successful implementation strategies.
* Recommended approach
* Successful implementation tip
{panel}

h3. Neutral Background Panel
{panel:borderColor=gray|titleBGColor=gray|title=Gray Neutral Panel}
Historical context or background information.
* Contextual detail
* Supporting information
{panel}

h2. Checklist Formatting Options

h3. Standard Bullet Checklist
* [ ] First task to complete
* [ ] Second task in progress
* [x] Completed task

h3. Confluence Checklist Macro
{checklist}
- [ ] Unstarted task
- [x] Completed task
- [ ] Pending task
{checklist}

h3. Highlighted Checklist
{panel:borderColor=green}
*Getting Started Checklist:*
* *[ ]* Identify critical business process
* *[ ]* Map process stages and outcomes
* *[ ]* Define business KPIs
* *[ ]* Link technical components
{panel}

h2. Emphasis Techniques

{panel:borderColor=blue}
*Bold Key Terms*: Use for critical concepts
_Italic for Subtle Emphasis_: Used for nuanced points
*_Combination of Bold and Italic_*: For ultimate emphasis
{panel}

h2. Callout Examples

{note}
Important note that stands out from the main content.
{note}

{warning}
Warning about potential challenges or critical considerations.
{warning}
